column1: #Text=Samuel Osborn was again chosen Mayor on Saturday last, this being his third successive year.
#Text=Walkers ketch William foundered on the 29th ult. off Swanage.
#Text=The crew, Sydney Alford and William Gandry, took to the boat, and were shortly after picked up by a Danish vessel, bound for Swansea.
#Text=They were very kindly treated, and put ashore at Plymouth.
#Text=Penny Readings.— The first of these entertainments for this year took place on Friday evening at the Masonic Hall.
#Text=The programme was as follows :—Polka, "The British Volunteers," full band; "The Winter Evening" (Cooper), read by Mr.
#Text=Atkins ; glee, " Lifes a Bumper;" "The London Tailor" (Anon), read by Mr.
#Text=Lowers ; quick march, " The Forester," full band ; song and chorus, " Come where my love lies dreaming ;" extract from " Julius Cassar" (Shakspeare), read by Mr.
#Text=Woodman ; solo, cornet-a-piston ; trio, " Yes, Brothers, Yes ;" "The Winking Bachelor" (Anon), read by Mr.
#Text=The room was crowded, under the presidency of the worshipful the Mayor.
#Text=—llicliard Williams, mail contractor, was summoned by Mary Ann Cornish for an assault, and her husband was summoned for a like offence.
#Text=—These being cross summonses, both parties were cautioned and ordered to pay their own expenses.
#Text=—Collingwood, Clarke ; Ann and Elizabeth, Young, Cowes.
